  o.autoView();
});
```

Hi @cdmerritt, when you retrieve your tickets from Zendesk the `custom_fields` list should be populated with dictionaries representing your custom fields. You can read the values as follows (assuming a field id of 79177827):

```python
for ticket in zenpy_client.tickets.incremental(start_time=start_date):
    for field in ticket.custom_fields:
        if field['id'] == 79177827:
            print(field['value'])
```

Hope this helps!

