@kennethreitz As per you, is using a decorator a better approach here?

As per my comments in issue: https://github.com/kennethreitz/maya/issues/33, I was thinking that usage of decorator is not a good idea for comparison methods due to their frequent call in loops. Instead explicitly handling each exception is better choice.

Finally, the decision is between Performance V/S Best Practice. Let me know the factor which takes priority for you. I will update the PR accordingly.

