if pixel_lookup[format] is not None:
    pixels = pixel_lookup[format].convert_pixels(link_to_pixel_data)


```
I guess you could have a __init__ on the handler classes so that they can initialise and return success from the, and re-use the instance each time you need to decode a dicom file. May save a few ms.

