@arkkanoid Note the virtual in "virtual size", the actual size on disk for these to images combined will probably be around 1.6-1.75GB (depending on your app). I don't know a method to actually check my theory for this particular case, which is a shame...

My understanding is that moving onto a Dockerfile workflow will actually be worse if you have multiple apps. Yes you can optimize each app and maybe get the size down to 500MB / app, but there will be less/nothing shared, so in the end you will end up in more storage in registry (which gets amplified by factor 3), and more diskspace on actual nodes when pulling the image to run, and resutling in slower pulls as there will be more network traffic...

If one of the maintainers can confirm my logic that would be nice, just reassuring to me I still have a decent understanding of how Deis / docker works...

