The plain tuple is the same as (du/dx, dv/dx), or using the first column instead first row of the Jacobian. So I suspect if everything is transposed it would work out just fine.

@douglam, it appears that TenserFlow uses the du/dx, dv/dx convention. [1][2] Perhaps it is worthy mentioning the difference in the tutorial? 

[1] : Their vjp operator of FFT appears to be iFFT (identical to my derivations): https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/94f2229c9e4b4324a324330c8f419276eda7e503/tensorflow/python/ops/math_grad.py#L961 
[2] : Their vjp operator of Pow appears to be doing exactly the conjugate: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/94f2229c9e4b4324a324330c8f419276eda7e503/tensorflow/python/ops/math_grad.py#L678

